caption: Table 2: Long-term forecasting results on 7 real-world datasets in MSE and MAE. The best result is highlighted in bold, and the second best is highlighted with underline.
description: This table presents the mean squared error (MSE) and mean absolute error (MAE) for seven real-world datasets using various long-term forecasting models. The models include SSCNN (the proposed model), DLinear, Autoformer, SCNN, iTransformer, TimeMixer, PatchTST, TimesNet, and Crossformer.  The best and second-best results for each dataset and metric are highlighted for comparison.

caption: Table 3: Robustness of SSCNN performance. The results are obtained from five random seeds.
description: This table presents the robustness analysis of the SSCNN model's performance.  The MSE and MAE metrics are reported for seven different datasets across five different runs, each initialized with a different random seed. The consistency of the results across these runs demonstrates the stability and reliability of the SSCNN model.
